= section "Absolute Pronouns" do
  %p The absolute pronouns are special pronominal forms used in isolation, when the verb and environment they should appear in is completely implied by context. In particular, they are used in response to questions such as “Who...?” and “Which...?”. The phenominon is similar to the colloquial English habit of answering questions like “Who did this?” with “Me” in place of “I did”, or answering “Which do you want?” with “That one” in place of “I want that one”.
